# sudoers/sudoers - Sudoers rules for this plugin.
#
# This file is installed to /etc/sudoers.d/<NAME> during plugin installation,
# where NAME is the plugin's short name from plugin.cfg.
# It allows the "loxberry" user to run specific scripts as root without a password.
#
# IMPORTANT: All scripts placed in the plugin's sbin/ directory are automatically
# granted sudo access during installation - you do not need to list them here.
# Only add entries here for scripts outside of sbin/ that need root access.
#
# The placeholder REPLACELBPBINDIR is automatically replaced by the installer
# with the actual path to this plugin's bin/ directory.
# Other available placeholders:
#   REPLACELBPCGIDIR    -> webfrontend/cgi/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPHTMLDIR   -> webfrontend/html/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPTEMPLATEDIR -> templates/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPDATADIR   -> data/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPCONFIGDIR -> config/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPSBINDIR   -> sbin/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPBINDIR    -> bin/plugins/<folder>/
#   REPLACELBPPLUGINDIR -> <actual plugin folder name>

# Example: allow loxberry to run a specific script in bin/ as root
# %loxberry ALL = NOPASSWD: REPLACELBPBINDIR/script-that-needs-root.sh
